 14217}, {\"ngram\": \"high-stakes international basketball\", \"from\": 14221, \"to\": 14257}, {\"ngram\": \"Yuta Watanabe Remaining Roster\", \"from\": 14313, \"to\": 14343}, {\"ngram\": \"not?There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 14533, \"to\": 14546}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hachimura and Watanabe will be fun to watch as the leaders for this roster, and Tominaga who\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s coming off an impressive senior season with Nebraska could have a big game but it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s hard to see a world where they have enough firepower to beat anyone in their group.\", \"from\": 14583, \"to\": 14849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14583, \"end\": 14592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hachimura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\"}, {\"begin\": 14597, \"end\": 14605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Momo_Watanabe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0350675352666444e-27, \"text\": \"Watanabe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Momo_Watanabe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Momo_Watanabe\"}, {\"begin\": 14724, \"end\": 14732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nebraska_Cornhuskers_football\", \"score\": 0.750344063052626, \"rank\": 0.3327219461537735, \"text\": \"Nebraska\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nebraska_Cornhuskers_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nebraska_Cornhuskers_football\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the leaders\", \"from\": 14630, \"to\": 14641}, {\"ngram\": \"this roster\", \"from\": 14646, \"to\": 14657}, {\"ngram\": \"Tominaga\", \"from\": 14663, \"to\": 14671}, {\"ngram\": \"an impressive senior season\", \"from\": 14691, \"to\": 14718}, {\"ngram\": \"a big game\", \"from\": 14744, \"to\": 14754}, {\"ngram\": \"it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 14759, \"to\": 14765}, {\"ngram\": \"a world\", \"from\": 14778, \"to\": 14785}, {\"ngram\": \"enough firepower\", \"from\": 14802, \"to\": 14818}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 14827, \"to\": 14833}, {\"ngram\": \"their group\", \"from\": 14837, \"to\": 14848}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Basketball is on the rise in Japan, and their domestic league\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s recruitment of Yuta and German big-man Thiemann this summer is a sign of how much it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s growing, but it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s not translating to a competitive Olympic roster quite yet.\\u00c2 \\u00c2 Head Coach:Nelson Colon NBA Players:Jose Alvarado\\u00c2 Remaining Roster:Arnaldo Toro, Ismael Romero, Chris Ortiz, Stevie Thompson, Tremont Waters, George Conditt IV, Isaiah Pineiro, Jordan Howard, Gian Clavell, Aleem Ford, Davon Reed Do we expect them to advance?No - 4th Why or why not?Puerto Rico can be scrappy and they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve got a good dose of G League-level talent around Alvarado, but the logjam of significantly undersized guards that they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re dependent on for offense and creation simply doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t set them up to be a team that can compete at the level necessary at both ends of the floor.\\u00c2 They could beat South Sudan and steal third in this group, but their point differential against Serbia and Team USA will likely rule them out of one of the final quarterfinal places.\", \"from\": 14850, \"to\": 15870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14879, \"end\": 14884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.8047502845591331, \"rank\": 0.24257156469261176, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 14931, \"end\": 14935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuta_Nakamoto\", \"score\": 0.9999998052808413, \"rank\": 1.9471971